info.name: api
info.description:
This is the documentation of RESTful films api.

**Note that app generates links to s3, which used to be real links to pictures, stored in Amazon S3. Unfortunately, this feature is unavailable now, so you won't be able to get acces to uploaded images.**

item.name: Auth

request.description:
Pass "username" and "password" fields to register a new User

Request fields:

- username - string
    

- password - string (at least 8 characters)
    

Status Codes:

- 201 - Created
- 200 - Validation error

Pass "username" and "password" fields to get access and refresh JWT tokens

Request fields:

- Username
- Password
    

Status Codes:

- 200 - OK
- 401 - Unauthorized (incorrect credentials)

Pass refresh JWT token (it's automatically stored in {{refresh-jwt}} env variable when you login) to refresh the expired access token

Requirements:

- Valid refresh JWT
    

Status Codes:

- 200 - OK
- 401 - Unauthorized (incorrect token)

item.description:
The folder contains endpoints for user registration and authentication. Without authentication you won't be able to access any of other endpoints

Auth steps:

1. Register user (if needed) using "Register user" request
2. Loin into the system using your credentials. After this step you'll receive JWT token, which will be stored in env variable {{jwt}} automatically and then will be used in 'Authorization' header
3. Enjoy the rest of the rest apiðŸ¥´
    

P.S. If your token expires, you can refresh it by making a refresh request ("Login refresh") or just re-login.

P.P.S. When you register new User, service automatically created 2 default playlists ('Watch later' and 'Favourites'). You can neither delete them nor update their titles.

item.name: Films

request.description:
Pass "release_date_after" and "release_date_before" query parameters to get films with release date within given range.

Status Codes:

- 200 - ok
- 401 - Unauthorized
    

If incorrect parametrs are given, api responses with all the data

Pass "country" query parameter to get films list filtered by given country title

Status Codes:

- 200 - ok
- 401 - Unauthorized

Pass "genre" query parameters (one or many) to get films list filtered by given genres

Status Codes:

- 200 - ok
- 401 - Unauthorized

Pass "order_by=release_date" query parameter to get films list ordered by release date ascending

Status Codes:

- 200 - ok
- 401 - Unauthorized

Pass "order_by=-release_date" query parameter to get films list ordered by release date descending

Status Codes:

- 200 - ok
- 401 - Unauthorized

Pass "order_by=rating" query parameter to get films list ordered by rating ascending

Status Codes:

- 200 - ok
- 401 - Unauthorized

Pass "order_by=-rating" query parameter to get films list ordered by rating descending

Status Codes:

- 200 - ok
- 401 - Unauthorized
    

If incorrect parameter is given, api responses with data, ordered by PK

Returns list of films

Status Codes:

- 200 - ok
- 401 - Unauthorized

request.description:
Pass fields in form data to create new instance of the Film model

Request fields:

- title - string
- poster_image - Base 64 string of the image
- content_rating - string
- genres - list of slugs of related genres (optional)
- actors - list of slugs of related actors (optional)
- country - string
- release_date - date string in format YYYY-MM-DD
- director - string
- description - text
- studio - string
- screenshots - list of dictionaries with base 64 string of images
    

Status Codes:

- 201 - Created success
- 400 - Validation error
- 401 - Unauthorized
    

Note that this POST request has complicated nested structure so it can't be executed using form data. Instead you can use it as a raw json, which hurts a lot due to huge Base64 pictures

Pass fields in form data and film's slug to update instance of the Film model

Request fields:

Set up values for all fields if using PUT method, else it's up to you what to update (you can change from 0 to max fields)

Status Codes:

- 201 - Created success
- 400 - Validation error
- 401 - Unauthorized

Pass the slug to delete instance of the Film model

Status Codes:

- 200 - Ok
- 202 - Accepted
- 204 - No content
- 404 - Not found
- 401 - Unauthorized

Pass the slug to get specific film instance

Status codes:

- 200 - Ok
- 404 - Not found
- 401 - Unauthorized

Returns list of all films' countries, stored in the database

Status codes:

- 200 - OK
- 401 - Unauthorized

Pass query parameter "q" to get search result with films, filtered by given title

Status Codes:

- 200 - OK
- 401 - Unauthorized

App supports pagination. It works with all the models. Default page size - 10

You can change it using "page_size" query parameter.

To switch between available pages use "page" query parameter

Status Codes:

Pass fields in form data and primary key to update instance of the Actor model

item.name: Playlists

request.description:
Returns list of user's playlists

Status Codes:

- 200 - OK
- 401 - Unauthorized

Pass a slug to get specific playlist instance

Status codes:

- 200 - Ok
- 404 - Not found
- 401 - Unauthorized

Pass fields in form data to create new instance of the Playlist model

Request fields:

- title - string
- films - list of slugs of related films (optional)
    

Status Codes:

- 201 - Created success
- 400 - Validation error
- 401 - Unauthorized

Pass a slug to delete instance of the Playlist model

Status Codes:

- 200 - Ok
- 202 - Accepted
- 204 - No content
- 400 - Validation error (occurs when you try to delete default playlists or change their titles)
- 404 - Not found
- 401 - Unauthorized

Pass fields in form data and primary key to update instance of the Playlist model

Request fields:

Set up values for all fields if using PUT method, else it's up to you what to update (you can change from 0 to max fields)

Status Codes:

- 201 - Created (updated) success
    

- 400 - Validation error
    

- 401 - Unauthorized
    

Note that you can't change the title of default playlists

Pass query parameter "q" to get search result with playlists, filtered by given title

Status Codes:

- 200 - OK
- 401 - Unauthorized
